The paper proposes a framework that combines compressive sensing and machine learning for multi-dimensional signals. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on using compressive learning for object classification and face recognition tasks. Information theory is also a likely category, as the paper discusses the theoretical complexity analysis of the proposed framework. Multimedia and numerical analysis are less likely categories, but they could still be relevant due to the multi-dimensional nature of the signals and the need for efficient computation.
